im = cv.imread(r"D:\Academics\Semester 4\Machine Vision\Homeworks\Documents\Homework6\sudoku.png", cv.IMREAD_COLOR)
assert im is not None

gray = cv.cvtColor(im, cv.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
edges = cv.Canny(gray, 10, 60, apertureSize=3)
lines = cv.HoughLines(edges, 1, np.pi/180, 200)

for line in lines:
    rho, theta = line[0]
    a = np.cos(theta)
    b = np.sin(theta)
    x0, y0 = a*rho, b*rho
    x1, y1 = int(x0 + 1000*(-b)), int(y0 + 1000*(a))
    x2, y2 = int(x0 - 1000*(-b)), int(y0 - 1000*(a))
    cv.line(im, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (0, 0, 255), 2)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize = (18, 6))
ax[0].imshow(cv.cvtColor(gray, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[0].axis("off")
ax[0].set_title("Original SUDOKU Image")
ax[1].imshow(cv.cvtColor(edges, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[1].axis("off")
ax[1].set_title("Canny Edges Detected Image")
ax[2].imshow(cv.cvtColor(im, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[2].axis("off")
ax[2].set_title("Houghlines Fitted SUDOKU Image")
plt.show()

im = cv.imread(r"D:\Academics\Semester 4\Machine Vision\Homeworks\Documents\Homework6\coins.jpg", cv.IMREAD_COLOR)
img = im.copy()
assert im is not None

gray = cv.cvtColor(im, cv.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
circles = cv.HoughCircles(gray, cv.HOUGH_GRADIENT, 1, 50, param1=150, param2=60, minRadius=20, maxRadius=50)
circles = np.uint16(np.around(circles))
for i in circles[0, :]:
    #draw the outer circle
    cv.circle(im, (i[0], i[1]), i[2], (0, 255, 0), 2)
    #draw the center of the circle
    cv.circle(im, (i[0], i[1]), 2, (0, 0, 255), 3)
cv.imshow('Detected Circles', im)
cv.waitKey()
cv.destroyAllWindows()
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize = (12, 6))
ax[0].imshow(cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[0].set_title("Original Coins Image")
ax[0].axis("off")
ax[1].imshow(cv.cvtColor(im, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[1].set_title("Hough Circles Fitted Coins Image")
ax[1].axis("off")
plt.show()

imgl = cv.imread(r"D:\Academics\Semester 4\Machine Vision\Homeworks\Documents\Homework6\pic1.png", cv.IMREAD_REDUCED_GRAYSCALE_2)
assert imgl is not None
templ = cv.imread(r"D:\Academics\Semester 4\Machine Vision\Homeworks\Documents\Homework6\templ.png", cv.IMREAD_REDUCED_GRAYSCALE_2)
assert templ is not None

im_edges = cv.Canny(imgl, 50, 250)
templ_edges = cv.Canny(templ, 50, 250)
alg = cv.createGeneralizedHoughGuil()
alg.setTemplate(templ_edges)
alg.setAngleThresh(100000)
alg.setScaleThresh(40000)
alg.setPosThresh(1000)
alg.setAngleStep(1)
alg.setScaleStep(0.1)
alg.setMinScale(0.9)
alg.setMaxScale(1.1)
positions, votes = alg.detect(im_edges)

out = cv.cvtColor(imgl, cv.COLOR_BAYER_BG2BGR)
for x, y, scale, orientation in positions[0]:
    halfHeight = templ.shape[0] / 2. * scale
    halfWidth = templ.shape[1]/ 2. * scale
    p1 = (int(x - halfWidth), int(y - halfHeight))
    p2 = (int(x + halfWidth), int(y + halfHeight))
    print("x = {}, y = {}, scale = {}, orientation = {}, p1 = {}, p2 = {}".format(x, y, scale, orientation, p1, p2))
    cv.rectangle(out, p1, p2, (0, 0, 255))

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize = (18, 6))
ax[0].imshow(cv.cvtColor(imgl, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[0].axis("off")
ax[1].imshow(cv.cvtColor(templ, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[1].axis("off")
ax[2].imshow(cv.cvtColor(out, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[2].axis("off")
plt.show()

a, b, c, d = [0, 0, 1], [0, 1, 1], [1, 1, 1], [1, 0, 1]
X = np.array([a,b,c,d]).T

theta = np.pi * 30/180
s = 1

tx, ty = 1.5, 2.2
a11, a12, a21, a22 = 0.8, 1.2, 0.7, 1.5 
A = np.array([[a11, a12, tx], [a21, a22, ty], [0, 0, 1]])
Y = A @ X

tx, ty = 0.5, 2.2
B = np.array([[s*np.cos(theta), -s*np.sin(theta), tx], [s*np.sin(theta), s*np.cos(theta), ty], [0, 0, 1]])
Z = B @ X

theta = 0
s = 2
tx, ty = 1.5, 0
C = np.array([[s*np.cos(theta), -s*np.sin(theta), tx], [s*np.sin(theta), s*np.cos(theta), ty], [0, 0, 1]])
H = C @ X

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize = (6, 6))

x = np.append(X[0, :], X[0, 0])
y = np.append(X[1, :], X[1, 0])
ax.plot(x, y, color = 'g')
ax.set_aspect('equal')

x = np.append(Y[0, :], Y[0, 0])
y = np.append(Y[1, :], Y[1, 0])
ax.plot(x, y, color = 'r')
ax.set_aspect('equal')

x = np.append(Z[0, :], Z[0, 0])
y = np.append(Z[1, :], Z[1, 0])
ax.plot(x, y, color = 'r')
ax.set_aspect('equal')

x = np.append(H[0, :], H[0, 0])
y = np.append(H[1, :], H[1, 0])
ax.plot(x, y, color = 'r')
ax.set_aspect('equal')

plt.show()

im1 = cv.imread(r"D:\Academics\Semester 4\Machine Vision\Homeworks\Documents\Homework5\img1.ppm", cv.IMREAD_ANYCOLOR)
im5 = cv.imread(r"D:\Academics\Semester 4\Machine Vision\Homeworks\Documents\Homework5\img5.ppm", cv.IMREAD_ANYCOLOR)

H = []
with open(r"D:\Academics\Semester 4\Machine Vision\Homeworks\Documents\Homework5\H1to5p") as f:
    H = np.array([[float(h) for h in line.split()] for line in f])

im1to5 = cv.warpPerspective(im5, np.linalg.inv(H), (2000, 2000))

fog, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 6))

ax[0].imshow(cv.cvtColor(im1, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[0].set_title("Image 1")
ax[0].axis("off")
ax[1].imshow(cv.cvtColor(im5, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[1].set_title("Image 5")
ax[1].axis("off")
ax[2].imshow(cv.cvtColor(im1to5[:800, :1000], cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
ax[2].set_title("Warped Image (image 1 to image 5)")
ax[2].axis("off")

plt.show()
